Package co.cookies.sdk

Provides SDK-level managers and utilities, which enable developers with access to underlying service clients.
  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    SDKConfiguration
    Defines the API surface for the main collection of configurable components that compose together to enable gRPC services hosted by Cookies.
    SDKServiceProvider
    Specifies the API surface of an object which provides access to Cookies service clients.
    ThrowingBiFunction<I1,​I2,​R,​E extends java.lang.Throwable>
    Defines the interface for a callable two-parameter function which declares itself the thrower of some checked exception.
    ThrowingCallable<R,​E extends java.lang.Throwable>
    Defines the interface for a callable function which declares itself the thrower of some checked exception.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    CookiesSDK
    Provides the main facade for acquiring a CookiesSDKManager, via CookiesSDK.builder().
    CookiesSDKManager
    Central manager for the Cookies SDK for Java; provides coordination via shared config and service support.
    CookiesSDKManager.Builder
    Builder object for preparing an immutable CookiesSDKManager manager.
    ExtensibleCookiesSDK<Settings extends SDKConfiguration>
    Provides an extension point for custom SDK implementations, along with a custom settings payload; additionally, acts as a self-configuring manager which may be used to spawn services.
    SDKUtil
    Provides static utilities used internally by the Cookies SDK.
